1
00:00:01,721 --> 00:00:04,601
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:45,321 --> 00:00:46,801
RYAN: We're never gonna find one.

3
00:00:46,881 --> 00:00:48,041
DOCTOR: Course we are!

4
00:00:48,121 --> 00:00:50,241
I've programmed
the detector specifically.

5
00:00:50,321 --> 00:00:52,001
I found seven last time I was here.

6
00:00:52,081 --> 00:00:53,521
GRAHAM: And how long did that take you?

7
00:00:53,601 --> 00:00:55,121
DOCTOR: It couldn't have been
more than a month.

8
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:58,121
Unless that was Seffilun 59.

9
00:00:58,801 --> 00:01:00,001
Which one is this?

10
00:01:00,081 --> 00:01:01,321
Seffilun 27.

11
00:01:01,761 --> 00:01:04,401
Maybe 59's the one
with the big pile of these.

12
00:01:04,641 --> 00:01:06,601
That's the problem with junk galaxies,

13
00:01:06,681 --> 00:01:09,001
all the planets look the same,
it's hard to keep track.

14
00:01:09,081 --> 00:01:12,121
If we've wasted the last four hours
on the wrong planet...

15
00:01:12,201 --> 00:01:16,001
Oi, who took you rain bathing
in the upward tropics of Kinstarno?

16
00:01:16,081 --> 00:01:17,961
Oh, no, no. Listen, that was amazing.

17
00:01:18,041 --> 00:01:21,361
I was just saying,
like needle, haystack.

18
00:01:21,761 --> 00:01:23,401
Yeah, you might be right.

19
00:01:23,481 --> 00:01:24,641
(BUZZING)

20
00:01:24,721 --> 00:01:26,761
No, hold on. I've found something.

21
00:01:28,641 --> 00:01:29,801
(WHIRRING)

22
00:01:29,881 --> 00:01:31,561
(GASPS)

23
00:01:31,721 --> 00:01:32,801
I'm sorry.

24
00:01:33,041 --> 00:01:34,201
YASMIN: What's he found?

25
00:01:34,601 --> 00:01:35,721
Nobody move.

26
00:01:38,841 --> 00:01:40,641
If I can keep it in temporal lock.

27
00:01:40,921 --> 00:01:43,081
No, there's too many sensors,
it won't work.

28
00:01:43,281 --> 00:01:44,561
It was camouflaged.

29
00:01:44,641 --> 00:01:46,681
This is someone's idea of a nasty joke.

30
00:01:46,761 --> 00:01:48,361
-What is it?
-Sonic mine.

31
00:01:48,761 --> 00:01:49,841
It's counting down.

32
00:01:49,921 --> 00:01:50,921
(BEEPING FASTER)

33
00:01:51,001 --> 00:01:53,201
-How long have we got?
-Three, two...

34
00:01:59,241 --> 00:02:00,681
WOMAN: I can't find their med tags.

35
00:02:00,761 --> 00:02:03,201
This is how rubbish I am at this.
You'd think it'd be simple enough.

36
00:02:03,281 --> 00:02:06,681
MAN: Mabli, stop beating yourself up.
I'm sure there's a simple explanation.

37
00:02:06,961 --> 00:02:07,961
(GASPS)

38
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:11,881
It's all right. You're safe.
Just don't make any sudden moves.

39
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:13,881
Your body will take
a moment to catch up.

40
00:02:13,961 --> 00:02:16,921
Can you point out your med tag for me,
I can't find it anywhere.

41
00:02:17,001 --> 00:02:18,001
Where are we?

42
00:02:18,081 --> 00:02:20,961
We're in hospital. They've just brought
us all round. You're the last one up.

43
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:22,441
YASMIN: We don't have med tags.

44
00:02:22,801 --> 00:02:24,801
Oh, it wasn't my mistake.

45
00:02:25,401 --> 00:02:26,401
Told you.

46
00:02:27,241 --> 00:02:28,641
Except you must have.

47
00:02:28,721 --> 00:02:32,641
We need your full bio. History,
allergies, fluid levels, life-span data.

48
00:02:32,721 --> 00:02:36,601
Basically, to help us avoid killing you.
Take it slow.

49
00:02:36,921 --> 00:02:38,041
There was...

50
00:02:38,121 --> 00:02:39,121
A sonic mine.

51
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:41,201
Yeah, the robot dredgers notified us

52
00:02:41,281 --> 00:02:42,721
as they were pulling you
from the debris.

53
00:02:42,801 --> 00:02:45,321
We've stabilised your vital organs.
You're lucky they got to you first.

54
00:02:45,401 --> 00:02:47,161
Stabilised my organs?
What happened to them?

55
00:02:47,241 --> 00:02:49,041
I've seen quite a few
sonic mine injuries here.

56
00:02:49,241 --> 00:02:51,281
They disrupt
your internal organic stability

57
00:02:51,361 --> 00:02:53,321
whilst churning up
the exterior environment.

58
00:02:53,401 --> 00:02:54,641
Tsuranga is actually agitating

59
00:02:54,721 --> 00:02:56,521
for the territories
to be swept more fully, but...

60
00:02:56,601 --> 00:02:58,561
(BEEPING)

61
00:02:58,961 --> 00:03:00,561
That doesn't make sense.

62
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:03,561
-Tsuranga.
-GRAHAM: What have they done?

63
00:03:03,881 --> 00:03:05,241
I know that name.

64
00:03:07,081 --> 00:03:08,161
(GASPING)

65
00:03:09,641 --> 00:03:11,881
Where have I heard the name "Tsuranga"?

66
00:03:12,881 --> 00:03:14,441
Whatever. I'm very grateful.

67
00:03:14,721 --> 00:03:15,961
Need to get back to our ship.

68
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:17,841
(GROANING) Come on, you lot.

69
00:03:18,441 --> 00:03:20,041
-MAN: Hey, come back.
-Which way is out?

70
00:03:20,281 --> 00:03:22,441
Can you return
to the assessment zone, please?

71
00:03:22,521 --> 00:03:24,561
We're not discharging you.
You need to rest.

72
00:03:24,641 --> 00:03:26,881
Well, I appreciate
how much you've looked after us,

73
00:03:27,561 --> 00:03:30,641
but my ship is very valuable.

74
00:03:31,001 --> 00:03:33,081
It's also my home. Our home.

75
00:03:33,961 --> 00:03:35,681
And I'm worried about leaving it here,

76
00:03:36,001 --> 00:03:39,361
on a junk planet
where people come and scavenge.

77
00:03:39,961 --> 00:03:42,281
I might never see it again.
And I've only just got it back.

78
00:03:42,361 --> 00:03:43,361
Wait here.

79
00:03:44,241 --> 00:03:45,321
This way out.

80
00:03:45,401 --> 00:03:46,761
Whether you agree or not,

81
00:03:46,841 --> 00:03:48,961
it is my responsibility
to protect the general.

82
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:51,641
I understand
your responsibilities, Ronan.

83
00:03:51,721 --> 00:03:53,081
Okay, I hear about them endlessly.

84
00:03:53,161 --> 00:03:54,761
Says the man who never wants
any of his own.

85
00:03:56,121 --> 00:03:57,121
Sorry.

86
00:03:57,201 --> 00:03:59,241
Looking for the exit. There's no signs.

87
00:03:59,321 --> 00:04:01,961
General Cicero's privacy indicators
are clearly on.

88
00:04:02,041 --> 00:04:04,601
Sorry, we're not really up
on privacy indicators.

89
00:04:04,681 --> 00:04:06,721
General Cicero? Not Eve Cicero?

90
00:04:06,801 --> 00:04:09,001
Keeba galaxy? Neuro Pilot?

91
00:04:09,161 --> 00:04:11,081
You're mentioned
in the Book of Celebrants.

92
00:04:11,161 --> 00:04:14,041
You helped defeat the Army of the Aeons
at the Battle of the Underkind.

93
00:04:14,361 --> 00:04:15,481
I was one of many.

94
00:04:15,561 --> 00:04:16,961
You're a bit of a legend though.

95
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:19,361
This is my brother, Durkas,
and my consort, Ronan.

96
00:04:19,441 --> 00:04:23,041
When she says consort,
she really means clone drone. Android.

97
00:04:23,121 --> 00:04:24,641
You can tell by the hair.

98
00:04:24,721 --> 00:04:25,721
Durkas.

99
00:04:27,001 --> 00:04:29,081
-And who are you?
-I'm the Doctor.

100
00:04:29,801 --> 00:04:31,521
Wait, I've heard that name.

101
00:04:31,601 --> 00:04:33,361
Aren't you in the Book of Celebrants?

102
00:04:33,441 --> 00:04:34,681
Isn't there a whole chapter about you?

103
00:04:34,761 --> 00:04:35,841
Me? No.

104
00:04:35,921 --> 00:04:37,041
Very common name.

105
00:04:37,121 --> 00:04:38,921
Anyway, lovely chatting, must be off.

106
00:04:39,001 --> 00:04:40,441
Hope you all get better soon.

107
00:04:42,841 --> 00:04:46,401
I'd say it was more of a volume
than a chapter.

108
00:04:46,601 --> 00:04:47,761
Just so you know.

109
00:04:48,921 --> 00:04:50,241
Oh, that bit hurts.

110
00:04:50,401 --> 00:04:52,721
Oh, that bit really hurts.

111
00:04:52,961 --> 00:04:54,121
Where is the exit?

112
00:04:54,201 --> 00:04:56,521
Why are there no signs for the exit?

113
00:04:59,481 --> 00:05:01,881
-Hi. Very sorry. Looking for the exit.
-Hello.

114
00:05:01,961 --> 00:05:04,201
Somebody needs to have a big rethink
on the signage in this building.

115
00:05:04,281 --> 00:05:05,641
I'd do it myself, but I need...

116
00:05:05,761 --> 00:05:07,161
(GROANING)

117
00:05:08,201 --> 00:05:10,441
My ectospleen hurts.

118
00:05:10,681 --> 00:05:12,281
I can feel it resettling.

119
00:05:12,361 --> 00:05:14,121
Oh, you're the sonic mine lot.

120
00:05:14,201 --> 00:05:15,601
It sounded pretty serious.

121
00:05:15,681 --> 00:05:17,001
-How're you feeling?
-Rough.

122
00:05:17,441 --> 00:05:18,441
What are you in for?

123
00:05:19,521 --> 00:05:20,521
Pregnant.

124
00:05:21,401 --> 00:05:23,561
Blimey, yes you are.

125
00:05:23,681 --> 00:05:24,681
Almost ready to pop.

126
00:05:24,761 --> 00:05:26,041
How did you get like that?

127
00:05:26,481 --> 00:05:31,001
On holiday, got involved with someone,
didn't take precautions. Like an idiot.

128
00:05:31,161 --> 00:05:32,721
So, what's that? Nine months?

129
00:05:32,801 --> 00:05:33,801
No, last week.

130
00:05:33,881 --> 00:05:35,721
-Last week?
-Oh, you're a Gifftan?

131
00:05:35,881 --> 00:05:38,161
Male pregnancies last a week.
Very intense.

132
00:05:38,241 --> 00:05:39,801
Yeah, feels like forever.

133
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,081
I'm a day overdue.

134
00:05:41,161 --> 00:05:44,601
They're thinking they might induce me
at Resus One, otherwise...

135
00:05:45,401 --> 00:05:47,241
Well, it wouldn't be good
for either of us.

136
00:05:47,921 --> 00:05:50,641
You're here. Look, you can't
keep disturbing all the other patients.

137
00:05:50,721 --> 00:05:53,161
Astos, found them.
They're here in Pod Two.

138
00:05:53,241 --> 00:05:54,881
We need to go now.
I'm sure you'll be fine.

139
00:05:54,961 --> 00:05:55,961
We'll be thinking of you.

140
00:05:56,601 --> 00:05:57,721
What do you mean "go"?

141
00:05:57,801 --> 00:05:59,041
How're you gonna do that?

142
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:01,801
-What do you mean?
-We have been trying to tell you.

143
00:06:05,001 --> 00:06:06,001
Yes.

144
00:06:07,361 --> 00:06:08,361
You have.

145
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,321
Vibrations.

146
00:06:12,601 --> 00:06:14,201
Too wrapped up in myself.

147
00:06:14,521 --> 00:06:16,841
Missed the vibrations.

148
00:06:16,921 --> 00:06:18,601
I was trying to break it to you gently.

149
00:06:18,681 --> 00:06:19,881
Tsuranga.

150
00:06:20,681 --> 00:06:22,641
This isn't a hospital,

151
00:06:23,241 --> 00:06:24,401
it's a ship.

152
00:06:25,241 --> 00:06:26,881
And we're already in flight.

153
00:06:26,961 --> 00:06:29,401
ASTOS: Tsuranga operates
emergency medical transport.

154
00:06:29,481 --> 00:06:31,081
This is a quad zone rescue craft.

155
00:06:31,401 --> 00:06:32,761
Like the Red Cross.

156
00:06:32,841 --> 00:06:34,921
You'll be fine.
We'll be at Resus One soon enough.

157
00:06:35,881 --> 00:06:37,641
-How long were we out for?
-ASTOS: Four days.

158
00:06:38,881 --> 00:06:40,561
Four days flight from the TARDIS.

159
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:42,321
I'm walking.

160
00:06:42,721 --> 00:06:43,721
(GROANING)

161
00:06:43,801 --> 00:06:44,921
No need to walk with me.

162
00:06:45,241 --> 00:06:46,561
I need to walk on my own.

163
00:06:46,921 --> 00:06:48,761
Four days. Walking.

164
00:06:49,081 --> 00:06:50,201
Come on, limbs.

165
00:06:50,281 --> 00:06:51,761
Have you got onboard teleport?

166
00:06:51,841 --> 00:06:54,761
No, but there's post-recuperation
onward teleport at Resus One.

167
00:06:54,841 --> 00:06:57,241
I don't wanna go to Resus One.
Let me talk to the pilot.

168
00:06:57,321 --> 00:06:58,561
Hey, it's not just you onboard.

169
00:06:59,121 --> 00:07:00,641
What are you doing? Don't touch that.

170
00:07:00,721 --> 00:07:01,801
Patients aren't allowed access

171
00:07:01,881 --> 00:07:04,001
to any onboard systems
or non-medical facilities.

172
00:07:04,081 --> 00:07:05,241
What were you worried about?

173
00:07:06,041 --> 00:07:07,521
Just as I was waking up you...

174
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:09,801
You saw something and you were worried.

175
00:07:09,881 --> 00:07:10,881
No.

176
00:07:11,161 --> 00:07:13,601
Ooh. Bad liar.
Must be difficult in your job.

177
00:07:13,681 --> 00:07:15,121
Hey, I'm an excellent liar.

178
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:17,281
-So, you were lying then?
-I didn't say that.

179
00:07:17,361 --> 00:07:19,241
See? Bad liar.

180
00:07:20,561 --> 00:07:22,161
Nav chamber. This way.

181
00:07:22,441 --> 00:07:24,481
(GROANING) Still hurts!

182
00:07:25,001 --> 00:07:27,481
Running can disrupt
the ongoing internal healing process.

183
00:07:30,521 --> 00:07:33,521
Enough now. You can't be in here.
I don't know what that device is,

184
00:07:33,601 --> 00:07:35,201
but if you don't leave
I have to restrain you.

185
00:07:35,361 --> 00:07:36,641
Where is the crew?

186
00:07:36,721 --> 00:07:38,921
Rescue crafts are automated.
It's a two-medic crew,

187
00:07:39,001 --> 00:07:41,081
just me and Mabli.
Our course is remotely programmed

188
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:42,761
from the Tsuranga hub at Resus One.

189
00:07:42,841 --> 00:07:44,121
How do we turn it around?

190
00:07:44,201 --> 00:07:47,001
We can't.
The course is remotely set and locked.

191
00:07:47,081 --> 00:07:48,921
The onboard crew don't have privileges
to unlock it.

192
00:07:49,001 --> 00:07:50,321
We'll see about privileges.

193
00:07:50,401 --> 00:07:52,401
Don't! If you interfere
with the navi system

194
00:07:52,481 --> 00:07:54,521
they'll take it
as an active hostility or hijack.

195
00:07:54,601 --> 00:07:55,841
They can detonate the craft.

196
00:07:55,921 --> 00:07:57,041
I'm not being hostile!

197
00:07:57,121 --> 00:07:59,601
Yes, you are!
You are being hostile and selfish.

198
00:07:59,681 --> 00:08:01,561
There are patients onboard
who need to get to Resus One

199
00:08:01,641 --> 00:08:02,761
as a matter of urgency.

200
00:08:02,841 --> 00:08:06,041
My job is to keep all of you safe.
You are stopping me from doing that.

201
00:08:11,481 --> 00:08:12,481
You're right.

202
00:08:15,081 --> 00:08:16,281
Of course, you're right.

203
00:08:18,401 --> 00:08:19,401
Sorry.

204
00:08:20,721 --> 00:08:22,761
That mine hit me harder than I thought.

205
00:08:22,841 --> 00:08:24,721
I've done 37 tours.

206
00:08:25,321 --> 00:08:26,761
We will get you back safe.

207
00:08:30,681 --> 00:08:31,921
Where are we?

208
00:08:32,481 --> 00:08:34,001
There's a lot of stuff out there.

209
00:08:34,081 --> 00:08:35,321
Space junk, asteroids...

210
00:08:35,401 --> 00:08:36,921
We're on the edges
of the Constant Division,

211
00:08:37,001 --> 00:08:38,561
that's what threw me back there.

212
00:08:38,641 --> 00:08:40,001
The routine usually
keeps us out of here.

213
00:08:40,281 --> 00:08:42,001
-Why?
-It's disputed territory.

214
00:08:42,081 --> 00:08:45,281
We're only just over the boundary
so nothing to worry about.

215
00:08:45,361 --> 00:08:46,401
So, what's that?

216
00:08:46,481 --> 00:08:47,481
What's what?

217
00:08:49,801 --> 00:08:51,321
Not sure.

218
00:08:58,041 --> 00:08:59,281
(CRASHING)

219
00:08:59,801 --> 00:09:00,961
Probably an asteroid shower.

220
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:03,761
(RAPID BEEPING)

221
00:09:03,841 --> 00:09:04,841
Shield breach.

222
00:09:05,081 --> 00:09:06,481
No, wait. Reconfiguring.

223
00:09:06,841 --> 00:09:08,001
Resealed and solid.

224
00:09:08,081 --> 00:09:09,561
But something breached it for a second.

225
00:09:10,241 --> 00:09:11,601
(THUDDING)

226
00:09:12,041 --> 00:09:14,521
(THUDDING CONTINUES)

227
00:09:16,441 --> 00:09:17,961
I'll check the system monitors.

228
00:09:22,601 --> 00:09:24,161
(THUDDING)

229
00:09:26,721 --> 00:09:28,481
Something is inside the shields.

230
00:09:29,281 --> 00:09:30,281
I'm sure it's nothing.

231
00:09:30,361 --> 00:09:31,641
Bad liar, Astos.

232
00:09:32,281 --> 00:09:33,481
Go back to your patient pod.

233
00:09:34,521 --> 00:09:35,601
I don't know your name.

234
00:09:35,681 --> 00:09:36,721
I'm the Doctor.

235
00:09:37,081 --> 00:09:38,881
-Are you kidding?
-Sometimes.

236
00:09:39,561 --> 00:09:40,881
But not right now.

237
00:09:41,001 --> 00:09:43,321
Tell me the ship's structure, Astos,
as quick as you can.

238
00:09:43,641 --> 00:09:45,201
Central walkway goes all the way around.

239
00:09:45,281 --> 00:09:46,801
We have an assessment area in the heart,

240
00:09:46,881 --> 00:09:48,961
three patient pods,
one emergency suite on the sides.

241
00:09:49,041 --> 00:09:50,681
We can perform
limited medical procedures,

242
00:09:50,761 --> 00:09:52,281
but our job is basically,
keep people alive

243
00:09:52,361 --> 00:09:53,561
till we can get them to a facility.

244
00:09:53,641 --> 00:09:54,881
Evacuation equipment?

245
00:09:54,961 --> 00:09:56,561
Two LifePods, port side and starboard.

246
00:09:56,641 --> 00:09:59,121
Maximum five per pod.
We're just within our occupancy limit.

247
00:09:59,201 --> 00:10:00,201
Oh, that's good.

248
00:10:00,401 --> 00:10:02,281
This ship was designed
for 100,000 tours.

249
00:10:02,361 --> 00:10:03,561
It can withstand a hell of a lot.

250
00:10:03,641 --> 00:10:05,401
Are you trying to reassure me
or yourself?

251
00:10:05,521 --> 00:10:06,961
(THUDDING AND BEEPING)

252
00:10:07,761 --> 00:10:10,681
-That's a breach alert.
-It's in the port side LifePod.

253
00:10:10,761 --> 00:10:12,761
-It can't be.
-Are there comms in the LifePod?

254
00:10:13,841 --> 00:10:15,121
(STATIC)

255
00:10:15,201 --> 00:10:16,201
(THUDDING)

256
00:10:19,481 --> 00:10:21,041
It's using the LifePod
as a way into the ship.

257
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:23,801
You know these territories.
What can it be? Whoa!

258
00:10:23,881 --> 00:10:25,321
That thing can really move.

259
00:10:25,401 --> 00:10:26,841
It's heading from the port side
to the starboard.

260
00:10:27,281 --> 00:10:29,561
Area around the starboard pod's
offline, I can't get a reading.

261
00:10:29,641 --> 00:10:30,681
We have to take a look.

262
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:35,401
Okay. You take port,
I'll check starboard.

263
00:10:35,481 --> 00:10:36,521
No, no, no. Too dangerous.

264
00:10:36,601 --> 00:10:38,081
You take port, I'll take starboard.

265
00:10:38,161 --> 00:10:39,161
You're not in charge here.

266
00:10:39,241 --> 00:10:42,361
This is my craft, you are my patient
and my responsibility.

267
00:10:42,441 --> 00:10:44,121
As is everyone else here.
You're still recovering.

268
00:10:44,201 --> 00:10:45,401
You're still in pain.

269
00:10:45,481 --> 00:10:47,881
I'll check starboard,
you check port side.

270
00:10:49,681 --> 00:10:51,081
I don't like being told what to do.

271
00:10:51,161 --> 00:10:52,161
Yeah.

272
00:10:52,281 --> 00:10:53,641
I'm getting that impression.

273
00:10:54,321 --> 00:10:55,521
Take a comm dock.

274
00:10:55,841 --> 00:10:56,841
Mabli already has one.

275
00:10:56,921 --> 00:10:59,041
Stay off her channel
while we work out what this is.

276
00:10:59,121 --> 00:11:00,401
She doesn't need to know about this yet.

277
00:11:00,481 --> 00:11:01,641
It's only her second tour.

278
00:11:01,721 --> 00:11:02,961
Neither do any of the other patients.

279
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:04,281
-Obviously.
-Obviously.

280
00:11:04,361 --> 00:11:05,921
Why am I trusting you, Doctor?

281
00:11:06,601 --> 00:11:08,161
You might be a bad liar, Astos,

282
00:11:08,401 --> 00:11:09,921
but you've got excellent instincts.

283
00:11:11,521 --> 00:11:12,721
Did you just buzz me?

284
00:11:12,801 --> 00:11:14,441
I'm requesting
further adrenaline blockers.

285
00:11:14,521 --> 00:11:15,681
-What, already?
-Yes.

286
00:11:15,961 --> 00:11:17,081
Let me check with Astos.

287
00:11:17,161 --> 00:11:19,601
No, you must supply them without delay.

288
00:11:20,241 --> 00:11:22,561
But we only carry a limited stock.
I'm not sure I'm allowed to.

289
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:23,961
The panels are down this way.

290
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:26,361
You know our status
and how Keeba Central regard us.

291
00:11:26,441 --> 00:11:28,281
We would not
ideally register a complaint

292
00:11:28,361 --> 00:11:30,121
against someone
so early in their career.

293
00:11:32,841 --> 00:11:34,281
Let's get them, then.

294
00:11:39,281 --> 00:11:41,761
I think that's staff only.

295
00:11:44,361 --> 00:11:45,601
Yeah.

296
00:11:47,801 --> 00:11:50,641
(SIGHING) I'm trying to figure out
what to do next.

297
00:11:51,721 --> 00:11:53,401
Deny everything or...

298
00:11:55,201 --> 00:11:56,601
Ask you to turn a blind eye?

299
00:11:56,681 --> 00:11:58,801
I see your problem. Yeah.

300
00:11:59,321 --> 00:12:01,801
Generally, truth is always
your best option.

301
00:12:03,921 --> 00:12:06,761
I was trying to hack
into my sister's medical records.

302
00:12:06,841 --> 00:12:10,361
Well, we've all hacked
into our loved ones confidential records

303
00:12:10,441 --> 00:12:12,121
at one stage or another, haven't we?

304
00:12:12,561 --> 00:12:13,561
(SCOFFING)

305
00:12:13,641 --> 00:12:14,881
Can I ask why?

306
00:12:15,601 --> 00:12:17,201
Well, she's lying to me.

307
00:12:17,401 --> 00:12:18,401
About...

308
00:12:19,281 --> 00:12:20,601
About what's wrong with her.

309
00:12:22,441 --> 00:12:24,241
She might have good reason for that.

310
00:12:25,761 --> 00:12:28,121
I know the reason.
She's a control freak.

311
00:12:28,201 --> 00:12:29,641
Even to her own little brother.

312
00:12:29,881 --> 00:12:32,441
The most decorated General
in Keeba history,

313
00:12:32,681 --> 00:12:36,841
907 days in continual flight,
on residual energy.

314
00:12:36,961 --> 00:12:40,201
Fighting the Ayonians,
saving our species.

315
00:12:41,841 --> 00:12:43,281
So, what do you do then?

316
00:12:43,521 --> 00:12:44,521
Me, I'm...

317
00:12:45,001 --> 00:12:46,001
-Engineer.
-Oh.

318
00:12:47,561 --> 00:12:48,561
Yeah.

319
00:12:48,841 --> 00:12:51,961
I have to fix the things
pilots like my sister tend to wreck.

320
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:53,521
And she looks down on me for it.

321
00:12:54,121 --> 00:12:55,281
And she always will.

322
00:12:56,961 --> 00:12:59,641
(DOCTOR PANTING)

323
00:12:59,841 --> 00:13:01,801
(CREAKING)

324
00:13:07,201 --> 00:13:08,521
DOCTOR: See anything, Astos?

325
00:13:08,601 --> 00:13:09,841
Nothing so far.

326
00:13:11,321 --> 00:13:12,321
DOCTOR: Me neither.

327
00:13:12,401 --> 00:13:13,761
ASYOS: The LifePod
is just around the corner.

328
00:13:13,841 --> 00:13:14,881
Me too.

329
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:18,161
DOCTOR: Go carefully. Whatever
this thing is, it can move very fast.

330
00:13:18,241 --> 00:13:19,921
The power has been shorted
around the LifePod.

331
00:13:20,441 --> 00:13:22,241
The power has gone out in this section.

332
00:13:23,521 --> 00:13:25,241
ASTOS: You need to check
if the pod is still secure.

333
00:13:26,401 --> 00:13:27,681
DOCTOR: The system is all drained.

334
00:13:32,801 --> 00:13:35,641
ASTOS: No sign of anything here, so far.
How about you?

335
00:13:36,761 --> 00:13:37,761
(GASPING)

336
00:13:38,761 --> 00:13:39,761
Astos,

337
00:13:40,161 --> 00:13:42,801
the port side LifePod, it's gone.

338
00:13:43,081 --> 00:13:45,281
-Jettisoned.
-Understood.

339
00:13:45,361 --> 00:13:47,361
(RATTLING)

340
00:13:49,441 --> 00:13:51,241
Doctor, it's here.

341
00:13:51,521 --> 00:13:52,841
It's inside this pod.

342
00:13:52,921 --> 00:13:55,841
Don't engage with it.
Stay where you are. We need you safe.

343
00:13:59,441 --> 00:14:00,481
Astos, what's happening there?

344
00:14:01,401 --> 00:14:04,401
Astos? Are you listening to me?
Do not engage.

345
00:14:10,081 --> 00:14:11,081
No, no, don't!

346
00:14:11,481 --> 00:14:13,841
COMPUTER: LifePod active,
disengaging.

347
00:14:13,921 --> 00:14:15,721
Use life-restraint straps, now.

348
00:14:16,081 --> 00:14:18,281
Astos, what's happening?

349
00:14:18,361 --> 00:14:19,521
Rookie mistake.

350
00:14:20,961 --> 00:14:22,241
It's jettisoning the pod.

351
00:14:22,681 --> 00:14:24,321
The internal controls are broken.

352
00:14:25,601 --> 00:14:26,681
And I'm inside.

353
00:14:28,441 --> 00:14:30,281
COMPUTER: Systems malfunction.

354
00:14:31,721 --> 00:14:32,841
Currently unavailable.

355
00:14:32,921 --> 00:14:34,521
Hold on. I'm coming.

356
00:14:35,881 --> 00:14:37,521
COMPUTER: Evacuation, critical

357
00:14:37,601 --> 00:14:39,361
Mabli. Mabli!

358
00:14:39,441 --> 00:14:41,961
Astos, I'm just with a patient.
Do you need something?

359
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:45,681
ASTOS: I'm sorry, Mabli.

360
00:14:46,281 --> 00:14:48,841
It tricked me. I can't get back.

361
00:14:49,401 --> 00:14:51,121
What are you talking about?
Get back from where?

362
00:14:51,441 --> 00:14:55,041
You can do this, Mabli.
You're good enough.

363
00:14:55,441 --> 00:14:58,561
You have to believe in yourself.
I believe in you.

364
00:14:58,641 --> 00:15:00,081
I always have.

365
00:15:11,881 --> 00:15:13,201
Astos?

366
00:15:13,281 --> 00:15:14,401
Astos!

367
00:15:16,641 --> 00:15:17,761
Astos?

368
00:15:18,241 --> 00:15:20,801
(PANTING)

369
00:15:29,641 --> 00:15:31,321
(GROWLING)

370
00:15:31,401 --> 00:15:32,681
(CLANKING)

371
00:15:42,641 --> 00:15:44,081
(GROWLING)

372
00:15:44,161 --> 00:15:46,521
-Where's Astos? Oh my saints!
-Doc, that bloke's lab our...

373
00:15:46,601 --> 00:15:47,801
What is that?

374
00:15:49,241 --> 00:15:50,601
(ROARS)

375
00:15:52,681 --> 00:15:53,681
I don't know.

376
00:15:53,801 --> 00:15:55,321
But it's incredibly dangerous.

377
00:15:56,081 --> 00:15:57,601
It jettisoned the LifePods.

378
00:15:59,521 --> 00:16:00,841
And it killed Astos.

379
00:16:01,521 --> 00:16:02,601
What?

380
00:16:02,681 --> 00:16:03,801
I'm sorry, Mabli.

381
00:16:03,881 --> 00:16:06,281
But it's down to us to get us
safely back to Resus One now.

382
00:16:06,721 --> 00:16:08,761
And you, off this ship!

383
00:16:08,841 --> 00:16:12,201
Back into space, right now.
Else you'll have me to deal with.

384
00:16:13,521 --> 00:16:14,521
(GROWLS)

385
00:16:18,161 --> 00:16:19,841
It just, sort of,
ignored you there, Doc.

386
00:16:19,921 --> 00:16:21,081
Got that, thanks, Graham.

387
00:16:21,761 --> 00:16:23,321
How is it eating all that stuff?

388
00:16:23,521 --> 00:16:25,041
What even is it?

389
00:16:26,681 --> 00:16:27,801
No idea.

390
00:16:28,281 --> 00:16:30,561
Hit the ship from the depths of space,

391
00:16:30,761 --> 00:16:32,521
so it can survive a vacuum.

392
00:16:32,761 --> 00:16:34,241
It doesn't need oxygen.

393
00:16:34,801 --> 00:16:38,921
And can digest pretty much whatever
it wants, by the looks of things.

394
00:16:40,721 --> 00:16:41,961
(CHOMPING)

395
00:16:42,041 --> 00:16:43,121
(GASPING)

396
00:16:43,201 --> 00:16:44,201
And it's got nerve.

397
00:16:44,281 --> 00:16:46,761
It's just ate my sonic!

398
00:16:51,401 --> 00:16:52,401
(CLICKS)

399
00:16:52,481 --> 00:16:54,401
-(SIGHS)
-(RUNNING FOOTSTEPS)

400
00:17:03,921 --> 00:17:04,921
Get them?

401
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,841
I think there may have been an incident.

402
00:17:11,721 --> 00:17:14,401
The ship's data banks,
I shouldn't let you in here,

403
00:17:14,481 --> 00:17:16,161
but I am and that's fine.

404
00:17:16,241 --> 00:17:17,601
I've already been in here with Astos.

405
00:17:17,681 --> 00:17:19,121
Has he really gone?

406
00:17:19,241 --> 00:17:20,441
I'm sorry, Mabli.

407
00:17:21,681 --> 00:17:25,561
He was one of the only people
who ever believed in me, including me.

408
00:17:25,641 --> 00:17:26,881
He was so kind.

409
00:17:26,961 --> 00:17:28,481
There aren't enough kind people.

410
00:17:28,561 --> 00:17:29,921
What would he want you to do now?

411
00:17:31,281 --> 00:17:33,161
Make sure everyone stays safe.

412
00:17:33,241 --> 00:17:34,241
You can do this.

413
00:17:34,321 --> 00:17:35,521
Right. Yeah.

414
00:17:35,881 --> 00:17:37,881
-I can.
-What did you want to show us?

415
00:17:37,961 --> 00:17:41,081
Well, if I sync my ocular recorders
with the data banks...

416
00:17:41,161 --> 00:17:43,801
Oh, yeah, sync
the old ocular recorders, it's obvious.

417
00:17:43,881 --> 00:17:46,961
All Tsuranga medics
are implanted with lenses,

418
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,761
so we can record
all treatments for training purposes,

419
00:17:49,841 --> 00:17:51,281
lawsuits, data records.

420
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:53,041
Like a posh version
of my uniform camera.

421
00:17:53,121 --> 00:17:56,241
Hang on. So, if this is the control deck
where is the rest of the crew?

422
00:17:56,601 --> 00:17:59,001
No crew. All automated.

423
00:17:59,201 --> 00:18:00,361
-So, it's just us.
-Yeah.

424
00:18:00,441 --> 00:18:01,921
-Alone.
-Yeah.

425
00:18:02,001 --> 00:18:03,161
-In space.
-Yeah.

426
00:18:03,241 --> 00:18:04,241
With that creature.

427
00:18:04,321 --> 00:18:06,601
-Yeah.
-Right.

428
00:18:06,681 --> 00:18:08,001
-I don't fancy its chances.
-Yeah.

429
00:18:08,281 --> 00:18:09,761
I back us every time.

430
00:18:10,601 --> 00:18:13,561
COMPUTER: Thank you for choosing
perils of the Constant Division.

431
00:18:13,641 --> 00:18:15,401
We know you have a choice of

432
00:18:15,481 --> 00:18:17,081
vid-briefings concerning
the most threatening of...

433
00:18:17,161 --> 00:18:18,761
Sorry. Here we go.

434
00:18:19,361 --> 00:18:22,201
COMPUTER:
Item Seven Alpha Cubed. Pting.

435
00:18:22,561 --> 00:18:23,681
ALL: Pting?

436
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,281
COMPUTER: Pting.

437
00:18:25,801 --> 00:18:27,401
Threat Level: Chalice.

438
00:18:27,481 --> 00:18:28,601
Is that bad?

439
00:18:28,681 --> 00:18:29,721
Worst one.

440
00:18:29,801 --> 00:18:31,361
One up from Beetroot.

441
00:18:31,441 --> 00:18:34,321
COMPUTER: ...the species,
if it is a species, birth or creation,

442
00:18:34,921 --> 00:18:39,001
many studies having failed, due to
the fatally violent nature of the Pting.

443
00:18:39,361 --> 00:18:42,041
No Pting has ever been kept
in captivity,

444
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:46,241
due to their ability to eat through any
material that would incarcerate them.

445
00:18:46,321 --> 00:18:50,521
While strictly non-carnivorous,
they devour all non-organic material.

446
00:18:50,601 --> 00:18:52,561
Well, at least that's something.

447
00:18:52,721 --> 00:18:54,721
Is it really? I mean, it won't eat us,

448
00:18:54,801 --> 00:18:56,881
but it will eat the ship we're on.

449
00:18:56,961 --> 00:19:00,881
...and while they may be momentarily
stunned are impossible to wound or kill.

450
00:19:00,961 --> 00:19:04,481
Pting's skin is understood to be toxic
to most lifeforms.

451
00:19:04,561 --> 00:19:06,241
Never touch a Pting directly.

452
00:19:06,321 --> 00:19:09,081
Ptings should never be restricted
to a confined space.

453
00:19:09,881 --> 00:19:12,921
Condensed advice,
never engage with Pting.

454
00:19:13,081 --> 00:19:14,881
Risk to life, ultimate.

455
00:19:17,361 --> 00:19:20,201
On the plus side,
I now feel very well informed.

456
00:19:20,561 --> 00:19:23,201
Seven minutes.
Get everyone into the assessment area.

457
00:19:23,281 --> 00:19:24,481
Why seven minutes?

458
00:19:24,561 --> 00:19:26,201
I need a moment to think.

459
00:19:34,441 --> 00:19:35,841
(PTING CHITTERS)

460
00:19:39,681 --> 00:19:40,681
What are you doing?

461
00:19:45,841 --> 00:19:47,001
Adrenaline blocker.

462
00:19:47,081 --> 00:19:49,361
You can't take adrenaline blockers
with corton fever.

463
00:19:49,441 --> 00:19:50,801
It's fine.

464
00:19:51,321 --> 00:19:53,881
You know, I knew
you were up to something.

465
00:19:53,961 --> 00:19:54,961
I knew you were lying.

466
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:57,041
-Durkas, I would respectfully...
-No, I would respectfully ask

467
00:19:57,121 --> 00:19:58,121
don't talk to me.

468
00:20:01,561 --> 00:20:04,041
-Hi. We're gonna need you to...
-Oh.

469
00:20:04,441 --> 00:20:05,441
Oh.

470
00:20:05,801 --> 00:20:06,801
Put your hand there.

471
00:20:06,881 --> 00:20:07,881
No, you're all right.

472
00:20:07,961 --> 00:20:10,601
Oh, go on, please.
Both of you, quick. It's kicking.

473
00:20:10,681 --> 00:20:12,241
Come on, it'll be nice to share it.

474
00:20:12,801 --> 00:20:14,121
Oh, wait for it.

475
00:20:14,921 --> 00:20:16,001
Wait for it.

476
00:20:16,721 --> 00:20:17,721
Oh!

477
00:20:19,921 --> 00:20:20,921
-Whoa.
-Whoa.

478
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:23,161
See? He likes you guys.

479
00:20:23,321 --> 00:20:24,321
Oh, and again.

480
00:20:25,081 --> 00:20:26,081
You know it's a boy?

481
00:20:26,161 --> 00:20:27,161
Of course, it is.

482
00:20:27,321 --> 00:20:30,001
Boys give birth to boys,
and girls give birth to girls.

483
00:20:30,081 --> 00:20:32,121
-That's how it is.
-Not where we come from.

484
00:20:32,201 --> 00:20:33,961
Ugh, how does that work?

485
00:20:35,641 --> 00:20:37,281
Do you wanna see my baby pics?

486
00:20:37,881 --> 00:20:40,281
We all need to be in the assessment area
in six minutes.

487
00:20:43,081 --> 00:20:44,081
Ha!

488
00:20:44,441 --> 00:20:45,881
One hour.

489
00:20:46,281 --> 00:20:47,881
Three hours.

490
00:20:47,961 --> 00:20:49,521
End of the first day.

491
00:20:49,961 --> 00:20:52,161
Mid second day.

492
00:20:52,241 --> 00:20:54,001
And, oh...

493
00:20:54,961 --> 00:20:56,241
Three hours ago.

494
00:20:57,361 --> 00:20:58,361
Mate...

495
00:21:00,561 --> 00:21:02,161
You're growing a person.

496
00:21:02,521 --> 00:21:03,921
Yeah.

497
00:21:04,321 --> 00:21:05,721
I couldn't do that.

498
00:21:07,121 --> 00:21:08,641
No, he really couldn't do that.

499
00:21:09,361 --> 00:21:10,361
Yeah.

500
00:21:10,441 --> 00:21:12,961
Almost seems a shame to give him away.

501
00:21:15,401 --> 00:21:16,601
That's what you're gonna do?

502
00:21:17,881 --> 00:21:20,281
Oh, I'm not fit to raise a kid.

503
00:21:20,361 --> 00:21:23,841
Besides, dark times right now.
Turbulent world.

504
00:21:23,921 --> 00:21:25,801
I'm not sure I'm his best option.

505
00:21:26,401 --> 00:21:28,201
I can't even operate my oven.

506
00:21:29,361 --> 00:21:30,361
But...

507
00:21:31,481 --> 00:21:32,761
Won't you miss him?

508
00:21:38,441 --> 00:21:41,241
Six minutes you said? I'll be there.

509
00:21:41,881 --> 00:21:42,881
Yeah.

510
00:21:45,681 --> 00:21:48,441
RYAN: He's the same age as my dad
must have been when he had me.

511
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:51,641
Same age as I am now.

512
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:54,961
Never really thought about it like that.

513
00:21:57,161 --> 00:21:59,121
I wouldn't be able to cope
having a kid now.

514
00:22:02,001 --> 00:22:03,721
When was the last time you saw your dad?

515
00:22:04,121 --> 00:22:05,121
A year ago.

516
00:22:06,161 --> 00:22:07,601
Didn't go well.

517
00:22:08,001 --> 00:22:09,361
Got angry with him.

518
00:22:11,041 --> 00:22:12,321
Why?

519
00:22:13,201 --> 00:22:15,001
He ducked out when I needed him.

520
00:22:16,361 --> 00:22:18,561
He's like a gap in my life.

521
00:22:18,841 --> 00:22:20,481
Even at Nan's funeral.

522
00:22:22,721 --> 00:22:24,201
Do you mind me asking?

523
00:22:26,441 --> 00:22:28,121
How did your mum die?

524
00:22:30,681 --> 00:22:32,001
(SIGHING)

525
00:22:35,121 --> 00:22:36,681
Washing up in the kitchen,

526
00:22:37,961 --> 00:22:39,841
massive heart attack, just...

527
00:22:41,001 --> 00:22:42,601
Just out on the floor.

528
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:43,961
God.

529
00:22:45,361 --> 00:22:46,681
Who found her?

530
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:50,201
Me.

531
00:22:53,201 --> 00:22:54,601
How old were you?

532
00:22:55,001 --> 00:22:56,081
Thirteen.

533
00:23:00,121 --> 00:23:01,121
Ryan,

534
00:23:02,761 --> 00:23:04,121
I'm so sorry.

535
00:23:04,681 --> 00:23:05,721
I never knew.

536
00:23:06,121 --> 00:23:08,601
I never knew life
threw that sort of stuff at you.

537
00:23:09,201 --> 00:23:13,321
I never knew that when it does,
sometimes adults don't cope either.

538
00:23:15,001 --> 00:23:16,001
Your dad.

539
00:23:16,321 --> 00:23:17,321
I get it.

540
00:23:18,801 --> 00:23:20,161
He loved her too.

541
00:23:21,481 --> 00:23:23,721
People always said
that I looked like her.

542
00:23:25,881 --> 00:23:27,481
He must have found that hard.

543
00:23:32,561 --> 00:23:34,961
Why am I even talking
about this? (SCOFFS)

544
00:23:37,081 --> 00:23:38,961
Come on.
Four minutes to the briefing.

545
00:23:39,841 --> 00:23:41,361
DOCTOR: Too fast to chase and capture.

546
00:23:41,441 --> 00:23:43,881
Too toxic to touch directly.

547
00:23:44,841 --> 00:23:46,041
It's a bit of a puzzle.

548
00:23:46,121 --> 00:23:47,281
It's gonna kill us all, isn't it?

549
00:23:47,361 --> 00:23:48,601
Oh, Mabli,
you went there way too quick.

550
00:23:48,681 --> 00:23:50,361
I said a puzzle, not a death sentence.

551
00:23:50,601 --> 00:23:51,601
I mean,

552
00:23:52,041 --> 00:23:55,761
it's a bit of a challenge,
and I can't quite see the solution yet,

553
00:23:55,841 --> 00:23:57,601
but that's life. Or medicine.

554
00:23:58,361 --> 00:24:00,161
Patients present problems,

555
00:24:00,241 --> 00:24:02,961
you figure them out
and come up with solutions.

556
00:24:03,041 --> 00:24:05,961
That's what this is,
a problem to be diagnosed.

557
00:24:06,161 --> 00:24:08,001
Medicine to be administered.

558
00:24:08,121 --> 00:24:10,321
You're a medic, I'm the Doctor.

559
00:24:10,401 --> 00:24:11,401
A doctor of medicine?

560
00:24:11,481 --> 00:24:13,281
Well, medicine, science,

561
00:24:13,361 --> 00:24:15,561
engineering, candy floss,

562
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:21,041
Lego, philosophy, music,
problems, people, hope.

563
00:24:21,121 --> 00:24:22,161
Mostly hope.

564
00:24:22,241 --> 00:24:24,121
I'm struggling to see much hope here.

565
00:24:24,801 --> 00:24:27,561
It doesn't just offer itself up,
you have to use your imagination.

566
00:24:27,641 --> 00:24:31,281
Imagine the solution,
and work to make it a reality.

567
00:24:31,521 --> 00:24:34,201
Whole worlds pivot
on acts of imagination.

568
00:24:34,281 --> 00:24:36,961
So, what are you imagining now?

569
00:24:38,321 --> 00:24:40,841
Broadly, I'm imagining
that thing off this ship.

570
00:24:40,921 --> 00:24:45,361
Specifically, I'm trying to imagine
the answer to the question.

571
00:24:46,481 --> 00:24:47,481
What does it want?

572
00:24:47,561 --> 00:24:48,761
Does it have to want anything?

573
00:24:48,841 --> 00:24:51,121
Every living thing,
from the tiniest to the largest,

574
00:24:51,201 --> 00:24:54,041
wants something. Food, survival, peace.

575
00:24:54,121 --> 00:24:55,881
But, the first thing it did
was kill Astos.

576
00:24:55,961 --> 00:24:57,641
That must be what it wants to do
to all of us.

577
00:24:57,721 --> 00:24:59,681
You know there's a much faster way
back to Resus One.

578
00:24:59,761 --> 00:25:01,521
Why is it routing us this way?

579
00:25:01,601 --> 00:25:05,881
Asteroid field. Fast moving asteroids
all around, really unpredictable.

580
00:25:05,961 --> 00:25:08,161
(ALARM BUZZING)

581
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:09,841
What are these?

582
00:25:09,921 --> 00:25:11,401
They are bad.

583
00:25:11,481 --> 00:25:15,281
This craft has over 5,000
different scan sensors,

584
00:25:15,401 --> 00:25:17,121
constantly feeding back to Resus One.

585
00:25:17,201 --> 00:25:20,401
They monitor everything,
both internally and externally.

586
00:25:20,481 --> 00:25:23,161
Check the routing is stable,
and there are no hostile forms,

587
00:25:23,241 --> 00:25:24,561
however microbial, on board.

588
00:25:24,641 --> 00:25:26,721
The systems have detected the Pting.

589
00:25:26,801 --> 00:25:29,441
They are asking us to confirm or deny
anything is wrong.

590
00:25:29,521 --> 00:25:31,641
We can't take a creature like that
back to Resus One.

591
00:25:31,721 --> 00:25:33,321
There's thousands
of vulnerable patients.

592
00:25:33,401 --> 00:25:34,521
And if we confirm it's onboard?

593
00:25:34,601 --> 00:25:35,841
They will recommend evacuation.

594
00:25:35,921 --> 00:25:36,961
But we can't evacuate.

595
00:25:37,041 --> 00:25:39,881
It goes straight to RST,
remote structural termination.

596
00:25:40,801 --> 00:25:42,121
They destroy the ship.

597
00:25:45,561 --> 00:25:46,561
Right.

598
00:25:49,161 --> 00:25:51,241
Nothing wrong. We're fine.

599
00:25:51,321 --> 00:25:52,801
We can't keep doing that.

600
00:25:52,881 --> 00:25:54,481
Three dismissals
and they don't believe you.

601
00:25:54,561 --> 00:25:56,241
Precautionary detonation.

602
00:25:56,361 --> 00:25:58,081
Oh, great. Who designed that?

603
00:25:58,161 --> 00:26:00,441
So, this ship either gets destroyed
by that creature,

604
00:26:00,521 --> 00:26:02,201
or by control from Resus One.

605
00:26:02,721 --> 00:26:03,721
Yeah.

606
00:26:04,961 --> 00:26:05,961
Sorry.

607
00:26:12,601 --> 00:26:13,841
(GRUNTS)

608
00:26:17,521 --> 00:26:19,521
You're probably wondering
why I called you all here.

609
00:26:22,561 --> 00:26:23,561
Sorry.

610
00:26:24,001 --> 00:26:25,161
Bit Poirot!

611
00:26:25,281 --> 00:26:29,081
I need to bring you all up to speed,
very directly, very succinctly.

612
00:26:29,441 --> 00:26:30,681
I can't sugarcoat this.

613
00:26:30,761 --> 00:26:33,001
-Where's the chief medic?
-Gone.

614
00:26:33,081 --> 00:26:36,041
Killed by an alien organism
called Piing that's come onboard.

615
00:26:36,121 --> 00:26:38,121
Very fast moving, very deadly,

616
00:26:38,201 --> 00:26:40,001
and it's eating its way
through the structure of the ship.

617
00:26:40,081 --> 00:26:42,721
Also, and this is the bit
you need to work on not panicking.

618
00:26:43,401 --> 00:26:44,681
It has jettisoned the LifePods.

619
00:26:44,761 --> 00:26:45,921
Oh.

620
00:26:46,801 --> 00:26:48,601
I'm the Doctor, these are my friends,

621
00:26:48,681 --> 00:26:51,321
Ryan, Graham and Yaz.

622
00:26:51,401 --> 00:26:53,361
You know Mabli, our very capable medic.

623
00:26:53,441 --> 00:26:56,921
We will pool all our brilliance
and get us all safely to Resus One.

624
00:27:04,761 --> 00:27:06,521
I thought there'd be more questions.

625
00:27:08,081 --> 00:27:10,841
I've encountered a Pting before,
it massacred my fleet.

626
00:27:11,441 --> 00:27:12,441
Okay.

627
00:27:12,681 --> 00:27:14,561
What did you learn about them?
What do they want?

628
00:27:14,641 --> 00:27:16,241
They kill, relentlessly.

629
00:27:17,281 --> 00:27:18,721
(RYAN GASPS)

630
00:27:20,201 --> 00:27:22,281
MABLI: It must have got
to the central systems.

631
00:27:22,961 --> 00:27:25,161
That means we'll soon lose
oxygen and heat.

632
00:27:25,241 --> 00:27:27,321
EVE: It'll go for whatever
is powering the craft next.

633
00:27:27,401 --> 00:27:29,001
We're on an anti-matter drive.

634
00:27:29,081 --> 00:27:31,081
We could use
stazers to defend ourselves.

635
00:27:31,161 --> 00:27:32,761
They can stun it briefly.
Got any onboard?

636
00:27:32,841 --> 00:27:34,521
A couple, I think, in here.

637
00:27:35,321 --> 00:27:36,681
If we're gonna live through this

638
00:27:36,801 --> 00:27:39,281
-protect the anti-matter drive.
-Protect the anti-matter drive. Snap!

639
00:27:40,721 --> 00:27:43,121
Can we get to Resus One
any faster than currently routed?

640
00:27:43,281 --> 00:27:45,321
Not without breaking
the ship's auto routing,

641
00:27:45,401 --> 00:27:47,561
which would send a signal back
to Resus One.

642
00:27:47,641 --> 00:27:49,401
And they go straight
to Hostility Protocols.

643
00:27:49,481 --> 00:27:52,281
I could create a false
positive route signal to send back.

644
00:27:52,361 --> 00:27:54,401
But there's no manual controls
in the nav chamber.

645
00:27:54,481 --> 00:27:56,121
-Show us.
-General...

646
00:27:56,201 --> 00:27:57,201
Shush now, Ronan. I know.

647
00:27:57,281 --> 00:27:58,881
We could go past the drive chamber
on the way.

648
00:27:58,961 --> 00:28:00,761
Durkas with me. Please?

649
00:28:00,841 --> 00:28:03,721
Um, is this a bad moment

650
00:28:03,801 --> 00:28:05,401
to mention my internal fluids
have broken?

651
00:28:05,801 --> 00:28:06,961
I think the baby is coming.

652
00:28:08,001 --> 00:28:09,161
Really sorry.

653
00:28:12,681 --> 00:28:14,761
The BirthBud is set up
in your PatientPod.

654
00:28:14,841 --> 00:28:17,241
-Let's get you back there.
-But it won't have any power.

655
00:28:17,321 --> 00:28:19,241
It's got a backup generator,
no need to panic.

656
00:28:20,881 --> 00:28:23,441
Would you two be my Dhulas?
I haven't got any Dhulas.

657
00:28:23,521 --> 00:28:25,401
-Do what?
-Dhulas, birth partners.

658
00:28:25,721 --> 00:28:27,681
She's brilliant,
but I need some men with me.

659
00:28:29,841 --> 00:28:32,201
-Yeah, we're blokes, aren't we?
-Yeah.

660
00:28:32,601 --> 00:28:34,881
-Yeah, yeah. All over it. Yeah.
-Come on.

661
00:28:35,161 --> 00:28:37,281
Right, now I'm imagining
you're sorting all this out?

662
00:28:37,361 --> 00:28:40,041
Me too. Be cautious,
it could be anywhere.

663
00:28:40,481 --> 00:28:41,481
Come on.

664
00:28:41,561 --> 00:28:43,801
-MABLI: You're fine.
-I need another adrenaline blocker.

665
00:28:43,881 --> 00:28:45,881
You used the last one, General.

666
00:28:46,641 --> 00:28:47,961
Everything okay?

667
00:28:48,881 --> 00:28:50,761
-Yeah.
-With me, please.

668
00:28:54,721 --> 00:28:55,961
Where do you think it is right now?

669
00:28:56,041 --> 00:28:57,041
I don't know.

670
00:28:57,201 --> 00:28:59,721
Can't trace it,
since the diagnostic systems drained.

671
00:28:59,921 --> 00:29:01,761
Doctor, quick word. Private.

672
00:29:02,641 --> 00:29:03,961
Catch you up, go on.

673
00:29:06,281 --> 00:29:08,081
Eve Cicero, her condition.

674
00:29:08,161 --> 00:29:10,161
-What about it?
-Patient confidentiality,

675
00:29:10,241 --> 00:29:11,481
I can't discuss with you,

676
00:29:11,561 --> 00:29:13,561
but if you're a doctor,
maybe you should examine her.

677
00:29:15,201 --> 00:29:16,201
I've got to go.

678
00:29:19,361 --> 00:29:20,881
Sorry, where are we?

679
00:29:20,961 --> 00:29:22,481
Oh, anti-matter drive.

680
00:29:22,601 --> 00:29:23,641
What century is this?

681
00:29:23,841 --> 00:29:26,321
-You're joking?
-No, we travel in time.

682
00:29:26,401 --> 00:29:28,041
-Are you joking now?
-No.

683
00:29:28,321 --> 00:29:30,441
-Sixty-seventh.
-Oh, nice century.

684
00:29:30,521 --> 00:29:32,721
Bit tricky in the middle.
Turns out all right in the end.

685
00:29:32,881 --> 00:29:35,281
See this, Yaz? Anti-matter drive.

686
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,281
Oh, I did a bit
on anti-matter at school.

687
00:29:38,601 --> 00:29:40,441
Never quite understood it.

688
00:29:40,601 --> 00:29:43,801
The thing with anti-matter is you
either have to find it or generate it.

689
00:29:43,881 --> 00:29:44,881
That's what this bit does.

690
00:29:44,961 --> 00:29:46,561
Particle accelerator.

691
00:29:46,641 --> 00:29:49,081
Like at CERN. We did that in physics.

692
00:29:49,241 --> 00:29:51,121
No, but the thing at CERN is massive.

693
00:29:51,201 --> 00:29:54,841
In your time, generating anti-matter
cost a massive amount of money.

694
00:29:54,921 --> 00:29:56,641
This is progress.

695
00:29:56,721 --> 00:29:59,521
Things get smaller, faster and cheaper.

696
00:29:59,601 --> 00:30:01,961
This is like the iPhone version
of CERN.

697
00:30:02,041 --> 00:30:05,841
Accelerating enough particles
to power this entire craft.

698
00:30:06,041 --> 00:30:07,041
So, how does it work?

699
00:30:07,361 --> 00:30:10,121
The particle accelerator
smashes the atoms together,

700
00:30:10,281 --> 00:30:13,801
like a little anti-matter factory
to produce positrons.

701
00:30:13,881 --> 00:30:17,881
Which are then stored very carefully
inside electric and magnetic fields.

702
00:30:18,121 --> 00:30:20,601
The positrons interact
with the fuel materials

703
00:30:20,721 --> 00:30:23,241
to produce heat, which produces thrust.

704
00:30:23,721 --> 00:30:25,321
It's pretty old school, this one.

705
00:30:25,841 --> 00:30:26,961
It's beautiful.

706
00:30:27,921 --> 00:30:30,761
Anti-matter powering
the movement of matter,

707
00:30:30,961 --> 00:30:33,721
bringing positrons into existence

708
00:30:33,921 --> 00:30:36,201
to move other forms of life
across space.

709
00:30:36,441 --> 00:30:37,441
I love it.

710
00:30:37,961 --> 00:30:39,361
Conceptually,

711
00:30:40,281 --> 00:30:41,721
and actually.

712
00:30:43,041 --> 00:30:45,561
Yaz, you have to keep this safe
from the Piing.

713
00:30:45,801 --> 00:30:47,241
If this drive gets destroyed,

714
00:30:47,321 --> 00:30:50,601
This ship will lose propulsion,
will drift endlessly while the Piing...

715
00:30:50,681 --> 00:30:52,961
I get it. It won't be good.

716
00:30:53,401 --> 00:30:54,481
Ronan can stay with you.

717
00:30:54,921 --> 00:30:57,321
No. General, my responsibility is to...

718
00:30:57,401 --> 00:30:59,721
Ronan, you're able to touch it
without it toxifying you.

719
00:30:59,801 --> 00:31:02,081
That's useful to all of us,
including me.

720
00:31:03,281 --> 00:31:04,281
Of course, General.

721
00:31:06,481 --> 00:31:08,601
You might need this, med blanket.

722
00:31:08,721 --> 00:31:11,441
Sterilised barrier.
67th century technology.

723
00:31:11,601 --> 00:31:13,161
In case you need to pick anything up.

724
00:31:17,081 --> 00:31:18,361
(THUDS)

725
00:31:22,001 --> 00:31:23,881
(ALARM BUZZES)

726
00:31:24,041 --> 00:31:25,321
(DOCTOR GASPING)

727
00:31:26,881 --> 00:31:28,281
Piing presence denied.

728
00:31:28,361 --> 00:31:29,761
Strike two, one left.

729
00:31:29,841 --> 00:31:32,121
Now, you two, see? A more direct route.

730
00:31:32,201 --> 00:31:34,841
Obviously, fast moving asteroids
and debris to avoid on the way,

731
00:31:34,921 --> 00:31:37,201
which is presumably
why the systems wanted to avoid it.

732
00:31:37,281 --> 00:31:40,481
Now, if I can rig up a cover signal
back to Resus One...

733
00:31:40,561 --> 00:31:42,161
Doctor, I'm a Neuro Pilot,

734
00:31:42,241 --> 00:31:44,681
my expertise is
in symbiotic neuro-piloting

735
00:31:44,761 --> 00:31:46,881
pulse systems at a push, but not this.

736
00:31:46,961 --> 00:31:48,561
Oh, I can make a rig
out of this chamber.

737
00:31:48,641 --> 00:31:49,641
No, you can't.

738
00:31:50,521 --> 00:31:53,641
You would't be able to make your way
through those asteroids even if I did.

739
00:31:54,041 --> 00:31:56,281
Yeah? Says you.

740
00:31:57,801 --> 00:31:59,841
-How long have I got?
-Literally, no time at all.

741
00:32:00,161 --> 00:32:01,361
Give me some space to work.

742
00:32:02,201 --> 00:32:04,001
Siblings... Bless.

743
00:32:07,321 --> 00:32:08,881
Why are you on this ship, General?

744
00:32:09,201 --> 00:32:11,761
Corton fever.
Contracted on my last duty.

745
00:32:11,841 --> 00:32:13,201
Can't quite shake it.

746
00:32:13,521 --> 00:32:14,721
What are you doing?

747
00:32:18,641 --> 00:32:22,641
Why would you be using
adrenaline blockers for Corton fever?

748
00:32:23,161 --> 00:32:24,361
How'd you know about the blockers?

749
00:32:24,441 --> 00:32:25,801
Your slow pulse, my really good hearing.

750
00:32:25,881 --> 00:32:27,241
You asked Ronan for some.

751
00:32:27,321 --> 00:32:28,841
It isn't Corton fever, is it?

752
00:32:30,481 --> 00:32:31,721
Is it Pilot's Heart?

753
00:32:33,081 --> 00:32:35,161
I'm sorry, Eve,
but if we're gonna survive this,

754
00:32:35,521 --> 00:32:37,281
you need to be honest with me.

755
00:32:44,441 --> 00:32:45,921
I started as a Pulse Pilot.

756
00:32:46,081 --> 00:32:49,801
I graduated to Neuro Fleet Commander
faster than anyone in Keeban history.

757
00:32:49,881 --> 00:32:52,401
I'm the most decorated general.

758
00:32:52,481 --> 00:32:53,841
I'm the poster woman.

759
00:32:54,801 --> 00:32:57,121
I cannot have Pilot's Heart.

760
00:32:57,681 --> 00:32:59,601
I cannot be that example to others.

761
00:32:59,681 --> 00:33:03,521
But you have, and you have been using
more and more blocker shots

762
00:33:03,601 --> 00:33:04,681
to get through the day.

763
00:33:04,761 --> 00:33:06,041
Trying to control

764
00:33:06,281 --> 00:33:08,721
the surges of adrenaline
around the heart.

765
00:33:10,201 --> 00:33:11,881
One big surge could kill me.

766
00:33:12,361 --> 00:33:13,521
Does Durkas know?

767
00:33:14,041 --> 00:33:15,041
I don't want him worrying.

768
00:33:15,321 --> 00:33:16,881
He's gonna find out sooner or later.

769
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:18,201
DURKAS: He already has.

770
00:33:18,921 --> 00:33:20,561
Not that he's surprised, just...

771
00:33:23,281 --> 00:33:24,521
Disappointed.

772
00:33:25,401 --> 00:33:27,201
-Durkas...
-We don't have time now.

773
00:33:27,721 --> 00:33:29,841
I've rigged a primitive piloting bypass,

774
00:33:29,921 --> 00:33:32,001
-combining pulse and neuro...
-I'll do it.

775
00:33:32,761 --> 00:33:33,961
Ever flown that way?

776
00:33:34,081 --> 00:33:35,081
No.

777
00:33:35,241 --> 00:33:36,241
But you can talk me through it.

778
00:33:36,321 --> 00:33:37,841
It takes people a dozen years to train.

779
00:33:38,161 --> 00:33:40,281
I really need to spend more time
in 67th century.

780
00:33:40,361 --> 00:33:41,921
I know how to do this.

781
00:33:43,161 --> 00:33:44,201
I'm not stopping now.

782
00:33:45,601 --> 00:33:48,241
Everyone is going to live. Including me.

783
00:33:49,081 --> 00:33:50,401
(GROANING)

784
00:33:51,041 --> 00:33:53,801
-Breathe deep, cockle.
-I am breathing.

785
00:33:53,881 --> 00:33:56,001
Oh, this really hurts!

786
00:33:56,081 --> 00:33:57,081
Yoss. Yoss.

787
00:33:57,441 --> 00:34:00,201
I'm giving you some stronger
pain management, it should help.

788
00:34:00,561 --> 00:34:02,081
(YOSS SCREAMING)

789
00:34:02,441 --> 00:34:03,881
Yeah. Yeah, that's better.

790
00:34:04,441 --> 00:34:06,401
Where's the BirthBud? Is it running?

791
00:34:06,481 --> 00:34:08,081
No, backup generator isn't working.

792
00:34:08,161 --> 00:34:09,521
(SCREAMING) What?

793
00:34:09,681 --> 00:34:12,081
I can't do this without a BirthBud!

794
00:34:12,161 --> 00:34:14,361
-Yoss, don't panic, mate.
-I am panicking.

795
00:34:14,441 --> 00:34:15,841
Which is why I'm telling you not to.

796
00:34:16,601 --> 00:34:17,881
Listen to your Dhulas.

797
00:34:17,961 --> 00:34:18,961
We're here for you.

798
00:34:19,521 --> 00:34:22,321
I don't even know you! Who are you?

799
00:34:22,401 --> 00:34:23,841
You're not the one about to have a baby

800
00:34:23,921 --> 00:34:27,321
you don't want, on a ship
without a BirthBud.

801
00:34:27,401 --> 00:34:29,001
-(GROANS)
-The baby is ready to come out.

802
00:34:29,081 --> 00:34:30,201
Oh, God.

803
00:34:30,281 --> 00:34:31,601
Oh. (GRUNTING)

804
00:34:40,681 --> 00:34:42,041
It's close.

805
00:34:42,121 --> 00:34:44,481
Just focus on protecting
the anti-matter drive.

806
00:34:48,921 --> 00:34:50,481
(SCREAMING)

807
00:34:51,921 --> 00:34:53,161
(YELPS)

808
00:34:53,241 --> 00:34:54,481
Stazers ready.

809
00:34:57,521 --> 00:34:59,601
-(SHIP CREAKING)
-(THUDDING)

810
00:35:02,681 --> 00:35:04,441
The creature is toying with us.

811
00:35:04,841 --> 00:35:06,281
(RUMBLING)

812
00:35:06,361 --> 00:35:07,641
(PTING GROWLING)

813
00:35:11,801 --> 00:35:13,641
-(SCREAMS)
-(GROWLING)

814
00:35:17,841 --> 00:35:19,921
I'll get it as far away
from the drive as I can.

815
00:35:20,001 --> 00:35:22,081
Be fast, the stun power
will only last a few seconds.

816
00:35:23,721 --> 00:35:26,121
Siobhan Chamberlain
with a goal kick for England.

817
00:35:29,401 --> 00:35:31,201
(CHITTERING)

818
00:35:31,721 --> 00:35:33,241
Okay, it's rigged.

819
00:35:33,321 --> 00:35:37,041
I've leeched some system power
off the anti-matter drive.

820
00:35:37,121 --> 00:35:39,601
Now if they can keep that
up and running,

821
00:35:40,081 --> 00:35:42,801
we'll have enough power
to keep basic systems going

822
00:35:42,881 --> 00:35:44,321
and still get to Resus One.

823
00:35:44,401 --> 00:35:47,281
That's if that thing
doesn't get in there

824
00:35:47,641 --> 00:35:49,281
and drain the energy.

825
00:35:49,641 --> 00:35:50,841
This isn't gonna work.

826
00:35:50,921 --> 00:35:51,961
Keep quiet, General.

827
00:35:52,281 --> 00:35:54,241
Trust your engineer

828
00:35:54,321 --> 00:35:55,681
and tell me you're well enough.

829
00:35:57,161 --> 00:35:58,521
I'm well enough.

830
00:35:59,841 --> 00:36:01,401
Now promise me that's true.

831
00:36:05,081 --> 00:36:08,201
You're gonna need every scrap
of energy you have.

832
00:36:09,921 --> 00:36:12,041
Cover signal transmitting to Resus One.

833
00:36:12,121 --> 00:36:15,121
Hopefully, bit of luck, they're still
gonna think they're in control.

834
00:36:16,721 --> 00:36:18,041
Durkas.

835
00:36:19,721 --> 00:36:21,001
You're a genius.

836
00:36:21,441 --> 00:36:23,241
The energy.

837
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:26,201
It doesn't wanna kill us,
it doesn't care about us.

838
00:36:26,281 --> 00:36:28,961
It wants the systems,
it wants the power.

839
00:36:29,121 --> 00:36:32,881
It didn't go for Astos,
it went for the life-support systems

840
00:36:32,961 --> 00:36:34,321
in the LifePod.

841
00:36:34,401 --> 00:36:37,201
It drained the lights and the power
and my sonic,

842
00:36:37,281 --> 00:36:41,561
it drains everything it eats.
That little creature seeks out

843
00:36:41,641 --> 00:36:44,281
and feasts on energy.

844
00:36:44,521 --> 00:36:46,641
That's why it homed-in on us here,

845
00:36:46,761 --> 00:36:49,441
pulsing with it in the wilds of space.

846
00:36:49,761 --> 00:36:51,161
Locked in, General.

847
00:36:51,561 --> 00:36:52,681
Try it out.

848
00:36:59,161 --> 00:37:00,441
I can see the course.

849
00:37:02,241 --> 00:37:03,801
I need to increase speed.

850
00:37:06,321 --> 00:37:08,201
Turning over control...

851
00:37:10,241 --> 00:37:11,401
It's all yours.

852
00:37:11,801 --> 00:37:13,721
-(RUMBLING)
-(GRUNTING)

853
00:37:13,801 --> 00:37:15,081
Eve.

854
00:37:24,681 --> 00:37:26,441
Still got it, boy.

855
00:37:30,001 --> 00:37:32,041
I've missed this so much.

856
00:37:32,361 --> 00:37:33,521
(EXHALES)

857
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:35,961
How is it?

858
00:37:36,041 --> 00:37:37,241
Rough.

859
00:37:38,081 --> 00:37:39,241
But it'll work.

860
00:37:39,761 --> 00:37:41,601
Take us in safely, General.

861
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:42,961
Nice and calm.

862
00:37:43,041 --> 00:37:45,041
(ALARM BLARING)

863
00:37:48,361 --> 00:37:50,361
Pting denial, strike three.

864
00:37:50,801 --> 00:37:52,641
After which, tricky.

865
00:37:53,241 --> 00:37:55,761
DURKAS: What will we do with the Piing
when we gel to Resus One?

866
00:37:56,041 --> 00:37:58,281
(ALARM BLARING)

867
00:37:58,361 --> 00:38:00,401
Nothing to worry about,
I'll deal with the Pting.

868
00:38:00,641 --> 00:38:01,921
Well, how are you gonna do that?

869
00:38:03,721 --> 00:38:07,041
Piing, bomb... No, can't get it.

870
00:38:07,121 --> 00:38:08,281
(SCREAMS)

871
00:38:08,361 --> 00:38:10,161
(GRUNTS) Still hurting.

872
00:38:10,961 --> 00:38:12,201
Yes.

873
00:38:12,881 --> 00:38:15,521
Maybe, maybe...

874
00:38:17,081 --> 00:38:19,081
It's me, I'm not a Pting.

875
00:38:19,721 --> 00:38:20,881
It was here.

876
00:38:21,481 --> 00:38:22,641
I got rid of it.

877
00:38:22,881 --> 00:38:25,761
-But it'll be coming back.
-What is the situation elsewhere?

878
00:38:25,841 --> 00:38:27,041
Eve's piloting the ship.

879
00:38:27,121 --> 00:38:28,881
Durkas is maintaining
controls and signals.

880
00:38:28,961 --> 00:38:31,081
You're guarding
the particle accelerator.

881
00:38:31,161 --> 00:38:32,441
-(EXPLOSION)
-(RUMBLING)

882
00:38:32,521 --> 00:38:35,561
Mabli, Graham and Ryan
are presumably delivering Yoss's baby.

883
00:38:35,641 --> 00:38:38,761
And the bomb's going to detonate.
I'm just going to move it away

884
00:38:38,841 --> 00:38:39,921
from this room.

885
00:38:40,001 --> 00:38:41,481
-Mind helping?
-Yes! |

886
00:38:43,801 --> 00:38:45,361
(GASPS) Clever sonic.

887
00:38:45,441 --> 00:38:46,721
Self-rebooting.

888
00:38:47,241 --> 00:38:48,441
There's a bomb in this room?

889
00:38:48,521 --> 00:38:49,761
Right in here.

890
00:38:50,801 --> 00:38:53,001
Mabli said that Resus One
would terminate the ship

891
00:38:53,081 --> 00:38:54,321
if they found the Pting on board.

892
00:38:54,401 --> 00:38:56,361
How would they do that?
We're too far for missiles.

893
00:38:56,881 --> 00:38:59,601
Has to be the same
for every Tsurangan rescue craft.

894
00:39:00,321 --> 00:39:01,761
It's built in.

895
00:39:02,321 --> 00:39:03,321
Self detonation.

896
00:39:03,401 --> 00:39:04,401
Bingo.

897
00:39:04,481 --> 00:39:07,241
Ten points for Yasmin Khan, and yes,
I am keeping score for all of you.

898
00:39:07,321 --> 00:39:08,721
Ronan, up your game.

899
00:39:09,361 --> 00:39:10,441
Jokes.

900
00:39:12,201 --> 00:39:13,681
So...

901
00:39:16,681 --> 00:39:18,241
You're interfering with the bomb?

902
00:39:18,321 --> 00:39:20,561
-Yes.
-Is it going to detonate?

903
00:39:20,641 --> 00:39:21,721
Yes.

904
00:39:21,801 --> 00:39:23,081
What will you do?

905
00:39:24,161 --> 00:39:25,521
Speed it up.

906
00:39:25,601 --> 00:39:27,121
To save our lives.

907
00:39:28,761 --> 00:39:31,241
Are you also experiencing
comprehension deficiency?

908
00:39:31,641 --> 00:39:34,041
Oh, every day right now, mate.

909
00:39:35,281 --> 00:39:36,761
Need to be so careful,

910
00:39:36,841 --> 00:39:38,361
tiny little device.

911
00:39:38,561 --> 00:39:40,401
Could blow us all to pieces.

912
00:39:40,481 --> 00:39:42,561
And I'm going to set it off.

913
00:39:44,041 --> 00:39:45,201
Ronan.

914
00:39:45,841 --> 00:39:47,361
Keep guard.

915
00:39:48,401 --> 00:39:51,721
Yaz, come on.

916
00:39:56,121 --> 00:39:57,241
Resus One in sight.

917
00:39:57,321 --> 00:39:59,081
We join the route
back in at this point,

918
00:39:59,161 --> 00:40:00,321
they won't know we've deviated.

919
00:40:00,921 --> 00:40:02,161
You okay?

920
00:40:02,641 --> 00:40:06,521
All those times
I thought I was going to die in battle,

921
00:40:06,801 --> 00:40:09,801
that you'd get a dispatch
and hear about it.

922
00:40:10,121 --> 00:40:11,601
I always felt so bad.

923
00:40:12,281 --> 00:40:13,561
But now...

924
00:40:14,401 --> 00:40:15,681
I'm glad you're here.

925
00:40:18,521 --> 00:40:20,201
(RUMBLING)

926
00:40:20,281 --> 00:40:21,721
(GRUNTING)

927
00:40:26,441 --> 00:40:27,561
Funny.

928
00:40:27,641 --> 00:40:29,121
I'm normally the one defusing the bomb.

929
00:40:30,641 --> 00:40:31,961
(GRUNTS)

930
00:40:35,841 --> 00:40:37,601
(BEEPING)

931
00:40:38,841 --> 00:40:40,841
Pick a number
between one and a hundred.

932
00:40:40,921 --> 00:40:42,081
Fifty one.

933
00:40:42,161 --> 00:40:44,161
Pentagonal number! Interesting.

934
00:40:46,561 --> 00:40:47,681
Get in that corner.

935
00:40:51,081 --> 00:40:52,321
What was the number for?

936
00:40:52,401 --> 00:40:54,721
Number of seconds before
the bomb goes off.

937
00:40:54,801 --> 00:40:56,361
I moved it forward a bit.

938
00:40:56,441 --> 00:40:57,561
What?

939
00:40:57,641 --> 00:40:58,841
I would've gone higher.

940
00:40:58,921 --> 00:41:01,641
Good number 51,
atomic number of antimony.

941
00:41:01,881 --> 00:41:04,361
The number of federalist papers
written by Alexander Hamilton.

942
00:41:04,441 --> 00:41:06,961
I love that show,
I've seen all 900 casts.

943
00:41:07,041 --> 00:41:08,081
(BEEPING)

944
00:41:10,601 --> 00:41:13,121
I'm giving you more gas, Yoss,
this will relax you.

945
00:41:13,201 --> 00:41:15,241
I've never been less relaxed
in all my life.

946
00:41:15,321 --> 00:41:17,161
I do not want to do this.

947
00:41:17,241 --> 00:41:19,041
Hey, hey, we're all here for you,
aren't we?

948
00:41:20,081 --> 00:41:21,321
Too right.

949
00:41:21,681 --> 00:41:24,601
Oh, yeah, I've seen every episode
of Call the Midwife.

950
00:41:24,681 --> 00:41:26,841
And he's descended from
an old Earth nurse, it's in his blood.

951
00:41:26,921 --> 00:41:28,321
-Every episode?
-Yeah, it's bang on,

952
00:41:28,401 --> 00:41:30,241
see whilst you've been mucking around
on YouTube,

953
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,321
I've been learning useful life skills.

954
00:41:32,401 --> 00:41:33,881
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

955
00:41:35,041 --> 00:41:36,601
I'm really trusting you on this bomb,

956
00:41:36,681 --> 00:41:37,681
but I don't know what you're doing.

957
00:41:37,761 --> 00:41:41,961
Think of the Piing as a mouse
and the bomb as a piece of cheese.

958
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:43,361
A very large piece of cheese

959
00:41:43,441 --> 00:41:45,201
about to explode
and take us all with it.

960
00:41:45,281 --> 00:41:46,561
It's not the perfect analogy,
I'll admit.

961
00:41:46,641 --> 00:41:48,041
You could've picked a bigger number.

962
00:41:48,321 --> 00:41:50,041
Where is it? Come on.

963
00:41:50,481 --> 00:41:51,881
So how do we do this then?

964
00:41:51,961 --> 00:41:53,881
Really straightforward,
cut open his stomach sac,

965
00:41:53,961 --> 00:41:55,121
reach in, remove the baby.

966
00:41:55,521 --> 00:41:56,721
Done.

967
00:41:56,801 --> 00:41:58,761
Cut him open?

968
00:41:58,841 --> 00:41:59,921
Won't that, like, hurt him?

969
00:42:00,001 --> 00:42:03,041
Oh, no, male Gifftan pregnancy sacs
don't have any pain sensors

970
00:42:03,121 --> 00:42:04,481
for precisely this reason.

971
00:42:04,561 --> 00:42:07,241
Yeah, but all the same, I mean,
cut open a bloke's stomach,

972
00:42:07,321 --> 00:42:08,801
do we have to?

973
00:42:08,881 --> 00:42:10,361
What, they didn't have that
on Gall The Midwife?

974
00:42:10,441 --> 00:42:12,481
I dunno, I always looked away
at the squeamish bits.

975
00:42:15,121 --> 00:42:17,921
As the bomb gets closer,
the energy is building

976
00:42:18,001 --> 00:42:19,041
getting ready to blow.

977
00:42:19,121 --> 00:42:21,681
The Piing must be attracted to that.

978
00:42:21,761 --> 00:42:24,401
Surely! That's what I've been working
on this whole time.

979
00:42:24,521 --> 00:42:27,641
Oh, please don't be wrong,
I'll be so embarrassed.

980
00:42:27,801 --> 00:42:29,121
And dead.

981
00:42:31,361 --> 00:42:32,721
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

982
00:42:32,801 --> 00:42:33,961
Doctor.

983
00:42:34,041 --> 00:42:36,881
I'm not bad, admit it,
I'm not bad, it's all in the timing.

984
00:42:40,281 --> 00:42:41,401
(SNARLING)

985
00:42:41,481 --> 00:42:42,561
When you're ready, mate.

986
00:42:46,681 --> 00:42:47,841
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

987
00:42:48,201 --> 00:42:49,481
Making the incision.

988
00:42:49,561 --> 00:42:51,161
(GRUNTING)

989
00:42:51,241 --> 00:42:52,961
Oh, I am never getting pregnant.

990
00:42:53,041 --> 00:42:54,881
All right now, opening up.

991
00:42:54,961 --> 00:42:57,401
Oh, I do not want this baby.

992
00:42:57,481 --> 00:42:58,841
I can't be a dad.

993
00:42:58,921 --> 00:43:00,681
Hey, none of that now.

994
00:43:00,761 --> 00:43:03,641
Listen to me, Yoss, you can do this.

995
00:43:03,961 --> 00:43:08,121
You're a good man, your baby,
your son will be lucky

996
00:43:08,201 --> 00:43:10,161
to have a good man like you as his dad.

997
00:43:10,481 --> 00:43:13,401
Starting now,
you're going to give him life.

998
00:43:13,681 --> 00:43:15,721
You're going to bring a person
into being, mate,

999
00:43:15,801 --> 00:43:16,961
that is epic.

1000
00:43:17,041 --> 00:43:18,321
I'm not ready.

1001
00:43:24,681 --> 00:43:26,481
Really? Get a shift on.

1002
00:43:32,721 --> 00:43:34,081
It ate it.

1003
00:43:34,161 --> 00:43:35,401
Wait for it.

1004
00:43:38,641 --> 00:43:39,841
(GROWLING)

1005
00:43:42,201 --> 00:43:44,161
(CHITTERING)

1006
00:43:46,481 --> 00:43:48,841
Absorbed, every bit of energy.

1007
00:43:48,921 --> 00:43:51,361
One massive, massive hit.

1008
00:43:51,441 --> 00:43:52,921
Bye-bye, Piing.

1009
00:43:53,481 --> 00:43:55,121
Intruder ejected.

1010
00:44:03,161 --> 00:44:05,361
First problem gone.

1011
00:44:05,721 --> 00:44:07,881
That should keep it fed
for a very long time.

1012
00:44:08,201 --> 00:44:09,441
We're still not home and dry though.

1013
00:44:09,521 --> 00:44:10,761
(BOTH GASPING)

1014
00:44:14,041 --> 00:44:15,641
I'm sorry.

1015
00:44:16,601 --> 00:44:18,001
For what?

1016
00:44:18,681 --> 00:44:21,121
I didn't tell you I was ill.

1017
00:44:22,441 --> 00:44:25,721
There's... Plenty of things
I've never told you.

1018
00:44:26,041 --> 00:44:28,841
Yeah, like what?

1019
00:44:29,161 --> 00:44:30,641
Like I love you.

1020
00:44:31,641 --> 00:44:33,681
I'm proud of you, sis.

1021
00:44:35,201 --> 00:44:37,041
I love you too, bro.

1022
00:44:38,001 --> 00:44:39,561
I'm sorry.

1023
00:44:46,441 --> 00:44:47,761
General.

1024
00:44:48,361 --> 00:44:49,801
Sac open.

1025
00:44:49,881 --> 00:44:52,681
Oh, shouldn't have looked,
can't unsee that.

1026
00:44:53,121 --> 00:44:55,321
-There's the baby.
-What does he look like?

1027
00:44:55,401 --> 00:44:56,761
Is he okay?

1028
00:44:56,841 --> 00:44:58,201
He's fine.

1029
00:44:58,281 --> 00:45:00,521
(PANTING)

1030
00:45:00,601 --> 00:45:02,441
Yoss, you don't have to be perfect.

1031
00:45:03,481 --> 00:45:05,201
You just have to be there.

1032
00:45:06,521 --> 00:45:07,921
(BABY CRYING)

1033
00:45:08,001 --> 00:45:09,961
It's okay, my darling.

1034
00:45:10,041 --> 00:45:11,801
-(CRYING)
-(SHUSHING)

1035
00:45:12,241 --> 00:45:14,601
You have to cut the cord simultaneously.

1036
00:45:15,881 --> 00:45:17,201
It's okay.

1037
00:45:18,121 --> 00:45:19,721
Come on, Professor Squeamish.

1038
00:45:19,801 --> 00:45:21,001
We're doing this.

1039
00:45:21,361 --> 00:45:23,121
-(RUMBLING)
-(GRUNTING)

1040
00:45:26,521 --> 00:45:28,561
-Three...
-Hang on.

1041
00:45:28,641 --> 00:45:31,001
Two, one...

1042
00:45:31,161 --> 00:45:32,281
Now.

1043
00:45:33,121 --> 00:45:34,481
YASMIN: (PANTING) Eve.

1044
00:45:35,041 --> 00:45:36,361
What happened?

1045
00:45:36,801 --> 00:45:38,521
Her heart couldn't take it.

1046
00:45:39,481 --> 00:45:41,081
She gave me control.

1047
00:45:41,801 --> 00:45:43,401
Do you know how to do this?

1048
00:45:44,521 --> 00:45:45,961
I'm a Cicero.

1049
00:45:46,481 --> 00:45:48,041
I've studied for this.

1050
00:45:48,321 --> 00:45:50,001
Coming into Resus One.

1051
00:45:50,281 --> 00:45:53,601
Resus One,
request emergency assistance landing.

1052
00:45:57,641 --> 00:45:59,161
Bringing her in safe.

1053
00:45:59,481 --> 00:46:00,841
Thank you.

1054
00:46:01,041 --> 00:46:02,401
Both.

1055
00:46:03,481 --> 00:46:05,041
Careful, dad.

1056
00:46:08,881 --> 00:46:10,361
Oh, my saints.

1057
00:46:10,841 --> 00:46:12,161
I did it.

1058
00:46:12,881 --> 00:46:14,281
It's a baby.

1059
00:46:14,361 --> 00:46:16,281
(BABY COOING)

1060
00:46:16,361 --> 00:46:17,721
Hello, mate.

1061
00:46:19,281 --> 00:46:20,721
I'm your dad.

1062
00:46:22,361 --> 00:46:23,721
I'm his dad.

1063
00:46:24,001 --> 00:46:26,001
-Yeah.
-(RUMBLING)

1064
00:46:27,961 --> 00:46:29,321
Nice one, Yoss.

1065
00:46:31,201 --> 00:46:32,641
You all right?

1066
00:46:33,441 --> 00:46:34,961
If your nan could see us now, eh?

1067
00:46:35,521 --> 00:46:38,281
-She'd be laughing herself crazy.
-Yeah!

1068
00:46:40,401 --> 00:46:41,721
No.

1069
00:46:59,401 --> 00:47:00,641
(SIGHS)

1070
00:47:01,721 --> 00:47:02,721
Um...

1071
00:47:03,281 --> 00:47:07,281
They say, quarantine scanning
and craft detox

1072
00:47:07,361 --> 00:47:09,161
should take no more
than three hours, then...

1073
00:47:09,481 --> 00:47:11,281
they'll admit us to the facility.

1074
00:47:11,881 --> 00:47:13,521
They're booking
your teleport to Seffilun,

1075
00:47:13,601 --> 00:47:15,601
soon as you've spoken
to the investigators.

1076
00:47:15,681 --> 00:47:17,121
Thank you, Mabli.

1077
00:47:18,041 --> 00:47:19,761
I'll be sure to tell them
how brilliant you were.

1078
00:47:21,281 --> 00:47:23,401
You all were.

1079
00:47:24,481 --> 00:47:26,201
Light in dark times.

1080
00:47:26,681 --> 00:47:27,881
People prevail.

1081
00:47:28,401 --> 00:47:30,121
Hope prevails.

1082
00:47:30,201 --> 00:47:32,321
(BABY CRYING)

1083
00:47:34,121 --> 00:47:36,721
-Have you got a name for the baby?
-Yeah.

1084
00:47:37,321 --> 00:47:38,881
In honour of you both,

1085
00:47:39,481 --> 00:47:41,841
I wanted to call him Avocado.

1086
00:47:41,921 --> 00:47:43,121
(SNORTS)

1087
00:47:43,681 --> 00:47:45,041
You what?

1088
00:47:45,121 --> 00:47:46,121
Avocado?

1089
00:47:46,201 --> 00:47:48,881
Yeah, after the ancient Earth hero.

1090
00:47:48,961 --> 00:47:50,281
Avocado Pear.

1091
00:47:50,361 --> 00:47:51,561
No, mate, that is a fruit.

1092
00:47:51,641 --> 00:47:53,281
No, it's a vegetable.

1093
00:47:53,361 --> 00:47:56,281
No, well, either way it's not a hero.

1094
00:47:56,721 --> 00:47:59,481
But we did it in school, you mean,

1095
00:47:59,561 --> 00:48:01,241
the Gifftan history logs are wrong?

1096
00:48:01,321 --> 00:48:02,681
Well, just a bit, I thought
he was gonna say,

1097
00:48:02,761 --> 00:48:03,961
you'd call him after us.

1098
00:48:04,201 --> 00:48:05,281
Graham-Ryan.

1099
00:48:05,721 --> 00:48:07,281
Or Ryan-Graham.

1100
00:48:07,641 --> 00:48:09,481
(LAUGHING) No.

1101
00:48:09,561 --> 00:48:11,361
He'd be a laughingstock.

1102
00:48:12,641 --> 00:48:13,841
Well, cheers.

1103
00:48:15,321 --> 00:48:17,041
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

1104
00:48:19,121 --> 00:48:21,241
If you're naming him,
does that mean you're gonna keep him?

1105
00:48:23,281 --> 00:48:25,361
I thought I'd give being a dad a try.

1106
00:48:28,321 --> 00:48:30,201
I'm gonna make mistakes, aren't I?

1107
00:48:30,641 --> 00:48:33,081
But I'll just keep going.

1108
00:48:39,801 --> 00:48:41,601
What happens to you now?

1109
00:48:42,321 --> 00:48:43,641
Without her?

1110
00:48:44,801 --> 00:48:46,281
I've come to the end of my service,

1111
00:48:46,361 --> 00:48:48,001
there is only shutdown.

1112
00:48:50,481 --> 00:48:51,841
I'm sorry, Ronan.

1113
00:48:52,281 --> 00:48:54,281
I wasn't always kind to you.

1114
00:48:55,201 --> 00:48:56,441
No.

1115
00:49:01,881 --> 00:49:03,121
(SIGHS)

1116
00:49:03,201 --> 00:49:04,641
You gave her great service.

1117
00:49:06,041 --> 00:49:07,321
As did you.

1118
00:49:10,481 --> 00:49:11,641
Yeah.

1119
00:49:13,601 --> 00:49:15,081
Will you in cant for her?

1120
00:49:17,001 --> 00:49:18,441
It would be my honour.

1121
00:49:19,681 --> 00:49:21,041
DOCTOR: Could we join you?

1122
00:49:21,641 --> 00:49:22,881
Please.

1123
00:49:34,081 --> 00:49:37,761
May the saints of all the stars
and constellations...

1124
00:49:38,801 --> 00:49:40,481
ALL: Bring you hope.

1125
00:49:41,361 --> 00:49:45,561
ALL: As they guide you out
of the dark and into the light.

1126
00:49:46,601 --> 00:49:49,241
ALL: On this voyage and in the next.

1127
00:49:49,641 --> 00:49:52,601
And all the journeys still to come.

1128
00:49:53,121 --> 00:49:55,561
DOCTOR: For now and ever more.

1129
00:49:58,561 --> 00:50:00,241
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

1130
00:50:28,361 --> 00:50:29,761
I want you to have this.

1131
00:50:30,561 --> 00:50:32,241
YASMIN: What's the point
in having a mate with a time machine

1132
00:50:32,321 --> 00:50:33,601
if you can't nip back
and can see your gran

1133
00:50:33,681 --> 00:50:34,721
when she were younger?

1134
00:50:34,801 --> 00:50:36,641
GRAHAM: 7947.
DOCTOR: We're in the middle of

1135
00:50:36,721 --> 00:50:38,161
the Partition of India.

